---
// src/pages/medicare-costs.astro — Costs pillar hub (M11). The silo head that
// ties the costs-irmaa spokes (and cost pages living in other silos) into one
// crawl path. Headline figures come from annualMedicareData so the pillar never
// drifts from the calculators it links to.
import ArticlePage from '../components/layout/ArticlePage.astro';
import { figuresFor } from '../data/annualMedicareData';
import { usd } from '../lib/formatters';
import type { PageContext } from '../types/Page';

const f = figuresFor();
const year = f.year;

const context: PageContext = {
  page: {
    title: `How Much Does Medicare Cost in ${year}? Premiums, Deductibles & Help | Vernal Medicare`,
    heading: `How Much Does Medicare Cost in ${year}?`,
    description: `A plain-English guide to Medicare costs in ${year}: Part A, B, and D premiums and deductibles, the IRMAA income surcharge, out-of-pocket limits, penalties, and the programs that lower your bill.`,
    taxonomy: { silo: 'costs-irmaa', tags: ['costs', 'part-a', 'part-b', 'part-d', 'irmaa', 'overview'], pillar: true },
    summary: `Medicare in ${year} has a few moving parts: the standard Part B premium is ${usd(f.partB.premium, { cents: true })}/month with a ${usd(f.partB.deductible)} deductible, Part A has a ${usd(f.partA.deductible)} hospital deductible, and Part D drug costs are capped at ${usd(f.partD.annualCap)} out of pocket. Higher earners pay an IRMAA surcharge; lower earners may pay far less through assistance programs. This hub walks through each piece and points you to the calculator for your own number.`,
    faqs: [
      { question: `What is the standard Medicare cost in ${year}?`, answer: `Most people pay the standard Part B premium of ${usd(f.partB.premium, { cents: true })}/month (Part A is usually premium-free if you worked 10+ years). On top of that you may have a Part D drug plan and, if you choose one, a Medigap or Medicare Advantage premium. Deductibles: ${usd(f.partA.deductible)} for Part A hospital stays and ${usd(f.partB.deductible)} for Part B.` },
      { question: 'Why is my Medicare more expensive than my neighbor’s?', answer: 'Usually income. Higher earners pay an IRMAA surcharge on Part B and Part D based on their income from two years ago. Two people with the same coverage can pay very different premiums purely because of IRMAA.' },
      { question: 'Can I lower what I pay for Medicare?', answer: 'Often, yes. Lower-income beneficiaries may qualify for Extra Help or a Medicare Savings Program that cuts premiums and drug costs. Higher earners can plan around IRMAA brackets. Choosing the right drug and supplement plan also matters — that’s where a local agent helps.' },
    ],
    sources: [
      { title: 'Medicare costs', url: 'https://www.medicare.gov/basics/costs/medicare-costs', publisher: 'Medicare.gov' },
    ],
    nextSteps: [
      { when: 'To see your real numbers,', action: 'run the Medicare cost estimator, then call us free to compare plans line by line.' },
    ],
  },
  meta: {
    canonical: 'https://vernalmedicare.com/medicare-costs.html',
    ogType: 'article',
    ogTitle: `How Much Does Medicare Cost in ${year}?`,
    ogDescription: `Premiums, deductibles, IRMAA, out-of-pocket limits, and the programs that lower your bill.`,
  },
  author: 'rocco',
  datePublished: '2026-06-30',
  lastUpdated: '2026-06-30',
  breadcrumb: [
    { name: 'Home', href: '/' },
    { name: 'Medicare Costs', href: '/medicare-costs.html' },
  ],
};
---

<ArticlePage context={context}>
  <p>"How much does Medicare cost?" doesn't have one answer — it depends on your parts, your income, and your plan choices. This page is the map. Below, each piece of your Medicare bill in <strong>{year}</strong>, with links to go deeper or run your own numbers.</p>

  <h2>The Building Blocks</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Part A (hospital)</strong> — usually premium-free if you or a spouse worked 10+ years. The {year} hospital deductible is <strong>{usd(f.partA.deductible)}</strong> per benefit period.</li>
    <li><strong>Part B (medical)</strong> — a standard premium of <strong>{usd(f.partB.premium, { cents: true })}/month</strong> and a <strong>{usd(f.partB.deductible)}</strong> annual deductible. See how it fits with Part A in <a href="medicare-part-a-vs-part-b.html">Part A vs Part B</a>.</li>
    <li><strong>Part D (drugs)</strong> — a plan premium (the {year} base is about {usd(f.partD.basePremium, { cents: true })}) plus copays, with out-of-pocket drug costs now <strong>capped at {usd(f.partD.annualCap)}</strong> a year and insulin at {usd(f.partD.insulinCap)}/month.</li>
    <li><strong>Medigap or Medicare Advantage</strong> — the coverage you add on top. Compare in our <a href="medicare-cost-estimator.html">cost estimator</a> and <a href="medicare-supplement-vs-advantage.html">Supplement vs Advantage</a> guide.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Estimate Your Own Cost</h2>
  <p>Numbers on a page only go so far. The <a href="medicare-cost-estimator.html">Medicare Cost Estimator</a> adds up premiums, deductibles, and expected out-of-pocket for a Medigap path versus a Medicare Advantage path, so you can compare real totals for your situation.</p>

  <h2>If Your Income Is Higher: IRMAA</h2>
  <p>Above {usd(f.irmaa.single[0])} in income (single) or {usd(f.irmaa.married[0])} (married), you pay an income surcharge called <a href="medicare-irmaa.html">IRMAA</a> on Part B and Part D. Look up the exact amount in the <a href="medicare-irmaa-brackets-2026.html">{year} IRMAA brackets</a>, <a href="medicare-irmaa-calculator.html">estimate yours</a>, and if you're over a line, learn <a href="how-to-reduce-medicare-irmaa.html">how to reduce it legally</a> or <a href="medicare-irmaa-appeal-ssa-44.html">appeal after an income drop</a>.</p>

  <h2>If Your Income Is Lower: Assistance</h2>
  <p>You may pay far less than the standard amounts. Start at the <a href="medicare-financial-assistance.html">help-paying-for-Medicare hub</a> — it sorts every program by income — or check the <a href="medicare-income-limits-2026.html">{year} income limits</a> directly. <a href="medicare-extra-help-utah.html">Extra Help</a> lowers Part D drug costs, and the <a href="medicare-savings-programs-utah.html">Medicare Savings Programs</a> (QMB, SLMB, QI) can pay your Part B premium outright. Struggling with drug costs specifically? See <a href="prescription-drug-assistance.html">prescription drug assistance</a>.</p>

  <h2>Caps and Penalties</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong><a href="medicare-out-of-pocket-maximum-2026.html">Out-of-pocket maximum</a></strong> — how Medicare Advantage caps your yearly exposure (Original Medicare alone has no cap).</li>
    <li><strong><a href="medicare-part-b-penalty-calculator.html">Late-enrollment penalties</a></strong> — a permanent surcharge for signing up late; estimate yours.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="medicare-plan-g-high-deductible.html">High-Deductible Plan G</a></strong> — a lower-premium way to buy Medigap protection.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Local Costs</h2>
  <p>Plan premiums and availability are local. See <a href="medicare-cost-uintah-county.html">what Medicare costs in Uintah County</a> for the plans actually offered here.</p>

  <p>Medicare's pieces add up differently for everyone. The fastest way to your real number is a quick conversation — <strong>call us free</strong> and we'll price it out with you, no obligation.</p>
</ArticlePage>
